{
  "message": "\ud83d\udc1b fix(drasi): address Copilot review feedback on #7868 (#7872) (#7875)\n\nFive follow-ups surfaced by the Copilot reviewer after PR #7868 merged:\n\n1. Gate node-level config controls behind demo mode. The gear button and\n   onConfigure handler on the Sources and Queries columns now render only\n   when !isLive \u2014 editing upstream resource config in-place against a\n   live Drasi deployment would diverge the UI state from reality.\n\n2. Skip setState when measured rects are unchanged. Without this,\n   ResizeObserver drives a setState on every observed mutation even when\n   the resulting NodeRect map is byte-identical, causing rerender churn\n   during window resize. rectsEqual compares container + per-node rects\n   and short-circuits setRects when equal.\n\n3. Prune ref entries for removed nodes. Switched from a Record of\n   RefObject<T> to callback refs (setSourceEl/setQueryEl/setReactionEl):\n   React calls the setter with the element on mount and with null on\n   unmount, so stale IDs drop out automatically. Previously the map\n   grew for the session lifetime as live resources came and went.\n\n4. Reusable ModalShell. The three demo modals (expand / source-config /\n   query-config) all rolled their own backdrop + keydown + panel wrapper.\n   Extracted into ModalShell with role=\"dialog\", aria-modal, and an\n   aria-labelledby pointing at a per-modal title id; added Escape-key\n   handler so keyboard dismissal works without relying on backdrop click.\n\n5. Keep React default import. After moving to named hook imports the\n   React.ReactNode references remained, so the default import is kept\n   alongside named ones rather than splitting into React.* vs bare hooks.\n\nBuild + ESLint clean on the file (the one remaining\nreact-hooks/set-state-in-effect warning on the selectedQueryId effect\nis pre-existing on main \u2014 not in scope for this PR).\n\nFixes #7872\n\nSigned-off-by: Andy Anderson <andy@clubanderson.com>",
